(Init-System)
!see: init-systemd

## Automatic start and sutdown of processes

the timing starts are defined in timer-unit-files  .timer
> systemctl list-timer  shows active timers

/usr/lib/systemd/system

*.timer and *.service files

### Cross
-> daemons

> systemctl reenable --now name.timer

This stuff needs a start like this:

#systemctl=systemCONTROL?
> systemctl start name      one time start
> systemctl stop name       

> systemctl status name
> systemctl restart name
> systemctl reload name     reload config

> systemctl enable name     start every time in future
> systemctl disable name    start 
